race.comment: THE MONA LISA (8) got a long way out her ground at Hawkesbury last time out before making good inroads to be beaten under two lengths. Will appreciate an extra 100m on a bigger track today. Cherry ripe at the third run back and can run a huge race at odds. EMPRESS OF JAPAN (3) closed well to be beaten under a length in the same race as THE MONA LISA at Hawkesbury recently. Scored a big win at this stage last prep. Looks a serious threat. EMBALLEE (6) closed well at the end of a mile at Gosford last Thursday. Very fit mare who is a contender - the wide draw is not so bad now after all the scratchings. VIRGIL'S GIFT (16) raced wide without cover then overcame interference to score an impressive win on debut over 1200m at Kembla last start. Early favourite and looks well and truly up to this. BEVERLY HILLS (14) led and was far too good at Newcastle recently. Scratched from an earlier shorter race to be stretched out to 1500m.
